sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) AS recording_count
FROM audio_recordings
WHERE common_name = 'Pacific Antwren';

SELECT DISTINCT common_name
FROM audio_recordings
WHERE quality_rating >= 4;

SELECT DISTINCT common_name
FROM audio_recordings
ORDER BY common_name;

external_knowledge:
- "Detailed records" refers to comprehensive information about each audio recording; 
- "Recording specifics" include file name, catalog number, common name, scientific name, length, recordist, record date, record time, country, location, elevation, record type, latitude, longitude, quality rating, equipment used, weather conditions, and notes; 
- "Total recordings by each recordist" implies the count of recordings made by each person; 
- "Expertise" refers to the area of expertise of the recordist; 
- "Average quality rating of the species" is the average quality of all recordings for a bird species; 
- "Conservation status" is the IUCN conservation status of the bird species; 
- "Most common recording type for the country" is the type of recording most frequently found in a given country;
- "Total accesses" refers to the number of times a recording has been accessed.
